CFF

Alignment Zones

Check if nodes are close to a zone, but not in or touching it.

This is a TTF, but this test is only for CFF fonts.

MS NID 6

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Kanit' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin' = NID 1 'Kanit Thin'.

Kanit Thin Italic (Kanit-ThinItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Kanit-ThinItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Kanit Thin Italic (Kanit-ThinItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Kanit' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin Italic' = NID 1 'Kanit Thin' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Kanit ExtraLight Regular (Kanit-ExtraLight.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Kanit-ExtraLight', Everything looks good.

Pass

This font software is the property of Monotype Imaging Inc., or one of its affiliated entities (collectively, Monotype) and its use by you is covered under the terms of a license agreement. You have obtained this font software either directly from Monotype or together with software distributed by one of the licensees of Monotype. This software is a valuable asset of Monotype. Unless you have entered into a specific license agreement granting you additional rights, your use of this software is limited by the terms of the actual license agreement you have entered into with Monotype. You may not copy or distribute this software. If you have any questions concerning your rights you should review the license agreement you received with the software. You can learn more about Monotype by clicking here: www.monotype.com.

Kanit ExtraLight Regular (Kanit-ExtraLight.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Kanit' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight' = NID 1 'Kanit ExtraLight'.

Pass

Kanit Light Regular (Kanit-Light.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.

NID 6 is 'Kanit-Light', Everything looks good.

Kanit Light Italic (Kanit-LightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Kanit-LightItalic', Everything looks good.

Kanit Light Italic (Kanit-LightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Kanit' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light Italic' = NID 1 'Kanit Light' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Kanit Regular (Kanit-Regular.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.

NID 6 is 'Kanit-Regular', Everything looks good.

Kanit Medium Regular (Kanit-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Kanit-Medium', Everything looks good.

Kanit Medium Regular (Kanit-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Kanit' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'Kanit Medium'.

Kanit Medium Italic (Kanit-MediumItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Kanit-MediumItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Kanit Medium Italic (Kanit-MediumItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Kanit' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium Italic' = NID 1 'Kanit Medium' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Kanit SemiBold Regular (Kanit-SemiBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Kanit' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold' = NID 1 'Kanit SemiBold'.

Kanit SemiBold Italic (Kanit-SemiBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Kanit' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold Italic' = NID 1 'Kanit SemiBold' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Kanit Bold (Kanit-Bold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Kanit-Bold', Everything looks good.

Pass

Kanit Bold Italic (Kanit-BoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Kanit-BoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Kanit ExtraBold Italic (Kanit-ExtraBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Kanit-ExtraBoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Kanit Black Regular (Kanit-Black.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Kanit-Black', Everything looks good.

Kanit Black Regular (Kanit-Black.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Kanit' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Black' = NID 1 'Kanit Black'.

Pass

Kanit Black Italic (Kanit-BlackItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Kanit-BlackItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Kanit Black Italic (Kanit-BlackItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Kanit' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Black Italic' = NID 1 'Kanit Black' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass
